OL,3,CTributes paid to 'proud father' who
OL,4,Cdied in alleged murder
OL,6,FTributes have been paid to a "proud
OL,7,Ffather" and "devoted brother" who died
OL,8,Fin hospital following an alleged
OL,9,Fserious assault in Bridgend.
OL,11,FDavid Rogers, 58, died in hospital
OL,12,Fafter an incident on Felindre Road,
OL,13,FPencoed, on Saturday, 28 February.
OL,15,FA man has since been charged with his
OL,16,Fmurder.
OL,18,FIn a statement released by South Wales
OL,19,FPolice, Mr Rogers' family said:
OL,20,F"Family meant everything to him."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/4
